    "body": "Fix for pytorch/pytorch#180908 to release/3.7.x.\r\n\r\nPR from main branch is: https://github.com/triton-lang/triton/pull/10132. See PR body for the split-cleanup design and the LLVM root cause (cf9b3bbb0986).\r\n\r\nFrom the main branch we made these changes due to differences between 3.7 and main\r\n  1. Removed the standalone runDeadIterArgElimination(m); line and its 2-line comment                \r\n  (runDeadIterArgElimination doesn't exist on 3.7.x).             \r\n  2. Added populateForOpDeadArgumentElimination(scfCleanup); as the first line of the SCF cleanup    \r\n  pattern set (3.7.x's older API for the same job).       \r\n\r\nVerified locally that crash kernel crashes with release/3.7.x HEAD but compiles correctly with this change    ",
